# Development Branch Workflow

This repository uses a two-branch model:

- **`dev`** — active development and testing (default branch for all AI and local work)
- **`main`** — stable production branch (Streamlit Cloud deployment)

## Before making changes

Always start from an up-to-date `dev` branch:

```bash
git checkout dev
git pull origin dev
```

Never commit or push directly to `main`.

## After completing a feature

```bash
git add .
git commit -m "feature description"
git push origin dev
```

Then report: commit hash, branch name (`dev`), and a short summary of changes.

Do **not** push to `main` automatically. When a feature is stable, provide merge instructions:

```bash
git checkout main
git pull origin main
git merge dev
git push origin main
```

## Rules

- Do not run `git push origin main` unless the user explicitly requests a production release.
- Do not force-push to `main`.
- Keep commits focused; exclude `__pycache__/`, `.env`, and secrets.
